This article describes update the microcode of AMD processors.

== Installation ==

=== Kernel ===
You need to activate the following kernel options:
{{Kernel||<pre>
Processor type and features  --->
    [*] /dev/cpu/microcode - microcode support
    [ ]   Intel microcode patch loading support
    [*]   AMD microcode patch loading support

Device Drivers  --->
    Generic Driver Options 
        CONFIG_EXTRA_FIRMWARE="amd-ucode/microcode_amd.bin amd-ucode/microcode_amd_fam15h.bin" 
        CONFIG_EXTRA_FIRMWARE_DIR="/lib/firmware"
</pre>}}

=== Software ===
You can now install {{Package|sys-firmware/amd-ucode}}:
{{Emerge|amd-ucode}}
{{Note|Because Dresden, Germany based Operating System Research Center team out of buissnes, please download from: http://pkgs.fedoraproject.org/repo/pkgs/microcode_ctl/amd-ucode-2012-09-10.tar/559bc355d3799538584add80df2996f0/amd-ucode-2012-09-10.tar}}

You can now reboot computer. Module microcode should autoload and upadte microcode of CPU from firmware directory.
